14. Real-World Example

An organization allows weak passwords without MFA.
A password spraying attack using Welcome@123 compromises multiple accounts.

Lesson: Strong passwords + MFA are critical.

15. Advantages of Understanding Password Attacks

Better defense planning

Improved security policies

Reduced breach risk

Stronger authentication systems

16. Limitations of Password Attacks

Time-consuming

Increasingly blocked by MFA

Easily detected with proper monitoring

17. Conclusion

Password attacks remain one of the most common attack vectors in cybersecurity. Understanding how these attacks work is essential for building strong authentication systems and defending against real-world threats.
